Depression sucks I've seen and done more than most it's been a tragic life and one of amazement. The rollercoaster ups and downs though through most of it, i wasn't alone but even in the greatest of times my darkness was and is the lonelyness overshadowing any light. I feel doomed no matter what. For it's loves light that escapes me...

I'm sorry you have Soo much feeling.

You did when you asked if maybe someone can bring something out in you. As for my opinion you definitely didn't get it besides opinions are.like assholes everyone has one. So unless you don't like free speech . Learn that . People have opinions and you don't have to like it or agree with it . But it's his or her right to express it. Now my opinion has changed . He's better of without a controlling narc.

After further thought . I began to reflect a bit on my ex an myself.. the hate part and going about it that way is a similar Tactic she used all I needed was the truth. The long distance thing I and maybe this other person felt as I did and do knowing long distance doesn't work. Or like was just tired of the road as I've spent my life out there. If you really want to make a go of it, it's a respect his wishes to seems like you wanted to have it your way. And he wasn't giving no more than you were.

This actually sounds like my ex but the time line is off. I miss her to the hilt and I loved her so much yet being treated like shit and her allowing others to sway her opinion was for the worst. I'd have gone the extra mile but not being treated and watching her lie to me and herself emotionally.
